<subSubSection id="9EE9475A417A5205DFD97354DCA284D3" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" type="type material">
<paragraph id="6EACDEF8B4843D34C8DB34CD64010DF9" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Type material.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E13A3AA9EE583F4B5C2A405F5101275" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis id="5B3197CE75B0229D6CF7542071FCBA08" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Holotype</emphasis>
male: Thailand, Nakhon Ratchasima Province, Pak Chong district, Musee Village, Wat Dewaroop Song Cave 3, 
<geoCoordinate id="EC2EA2C6231C561050D0558889697422" degrees="14" direction="north" minutes="33.714" orientation="latitude" precision="1" value="14.5619">14°33.714'N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="39B8A3B4B2C906B3E556CC2C293259EE" degrees="101" direction="east" minutes="24.049" orientation="longitude" precision="1" value="101.40082">101°24.049'E</geoCoordinate>
, 402 m a.s.l., 24 Oct. 2014, Yun-Chun Li and Zhi-Gang Chen leg., in MCWNU (Ms20141014-01). 
<emphasis id="5D8E74EC1FE96AEB932A533C8DF4DF17" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Paratypes</emphasis>
: 3 males, 7 females, 7 tritonymphs, collected with the holotype, in MCWNU (Ms20141014-01); 1 male, 2 females, 1 tritonymph, collected with the holotype, in MNHN.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8A1DCC47D5B3EB0DC830070079A16801" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="638C547D4A5E9E02E2AE5453AA9EF8C7" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4FEDEEBE643253C7F5CF526D89C21293" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">
Troglobiont habitus. This new species is distinguished from other members of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="11717A9AA77B4F61A6BE1E21B461B4AD" authorityName="Redikorzev" authorityYear="1938" class="Arachnida" family="Cheliferidae" genus="Metachelifer" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Metachelifer" order="Pseudoscorpionida" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C6796DE1CC974C98942F46E0443002AD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Metachelifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characters: carapace with 100-101 setae; coxal sac occupying 1/2 of coxal length; male anterior genital operculum without tubular setae; female anterior genital operculum with 31 setae (24 of them tubular) and two lyrifissures; posterior operculum with 12 setae, without lyrifissures.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FF4222717E1585D39F1FACFC19B2E053" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="2D355CAD8634D50F33B78E4C7665564B" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8ED0EAE555384257BC5B100875C15A0C" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Latinized adjective, derived from the last name of the collector, Zhi-Gang Chen.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CC3EC6240FAEA9EA0147166448B52F1D" pageId="0" pageNumber="171" type="description">
<paragraph id="3CA28E607CBBD898C5CF9C9DA1172526" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB7DA9FA6B22FFC8B06169B16A16B681" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis id="A7338FDA97B9FA8A0B5B7DD0C55566DA" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Adult male</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1E7188607280984A8613D5CCF4881C83" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. A, B Metachelifer cheni sp. nov., dorsal views A holotype male B paratype female C, D M. mahnerti sp. nov., dorsal views C holotype male D paratype female. Scale bar: 1.00 mm (A-D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.78808.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691638" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">5A</figureCitation>
). Carapace, pedipalps and tergites I-III brown, remaining parts yellowish brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4F5BC5A0BEEB6FE2EEAEBA252AC1A15C" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. A, B Metachelifer cheni sp. nov., dorsal views A holotype male B paratype female C, D M. mahnerti sp. nov., dorsal views C holotype male D paratype female. Scale bar: 1.00 mm (A-D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.78808.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691638" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">5A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B0D68F8E533693FF968C2F7CBBE2F275" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis id="8B4E651E29B1E036B47E4681C3C707C7" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Carapace</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7932D8B372D5A0C03A81FF62DB6EEBF0" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Metachelifer cheni sp. nov., holotype male (A-J) and paratype female (K) A carapace B left chelicera C right leg I, lateral view D right leg IV, lateral view E coxa IV, ventral view F palp (minus chela) G chela, retrolateral view H chela, dorsal view I male genital area J male genitalia, dorsal view K female genital area. Scale bars: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.78808.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691634" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">1A</figureCitation>
): 1.14-1.16 
<normalizedToken id="8B57E53D04923A0707DB6478E581C106" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than broad, with a pair of well-developed eyes, length of eyes 0.09 mm, breadth 0.03 mm, carapace surface evenly and strongly granular. Median and posterior furrows prominent, regularly granular. Dorsal setae of carapace, borne on larger but relatively inconspicuous tubercles. With 100-101 denticuloclavate setae, including 8 on anterior margin and 11-12 on posterior margin. 
<emphasis id="F91153F0D7A5A0DB174A772E2977B8A6" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Coxae</emphasis>
: manducatory process with 4 setae (1 long apical, 2 rather short subapical setae, and 1 suboral seta at base of medial margin). Pedipalpal coxa with 10 (non-denticulate) + 7-8 (denticulate) setae, coxa I 14-16, II 15, III 18-19, IV with an anterolateral process and 30-36 setae. Coxal sac occupying only 1/2 of coxal length, atrium well developed (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="515FFE77C6221BC4CCE5E028600C5196" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Metachelifer cheni sp. nov., holotype male (A-J) and paratype female (K) A carapace B left chelicera C right leg I, lateral view D right leg IV, lateral view E coxa IV, ventral view F palp (minus chela) G chela, retrolateral view H chela, dorsal view I male genital area J male genitalia, dorsal view K female genital area. Scale bars: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.78808.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691634" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">1E</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="1F9BFF39C2D87F8AA8E019E6E12D9EA2" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Chelicera</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="416B941A42F3AF333758C941CFD4C55E" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Metachelifer cheni sp. nov., holotype male (A-J) and paratype female (K) A carapace B left chelicera C right leg I, lateral view D right leg IV, lateral view E coxa IV, ventral view F palp (minus chela) G chela, retrolateral view H chela, dorsal view I male genital area J male genitalia, dorsal view K female genital area. Scale bars: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.78808.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691634" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">1B</figureCitation>
): 1.85-1.91 
<normalizedToken id="6C3CBCD5719195367CA8D223ABD22365" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than broad, hand with 5 setae and 1 lyrifissure dorsally, movable finger with 1 submedial seta (1 specimen with 2 submedial setae) and 2-3 teeth (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5C2776823C79CADA0EF66367CC73B988" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Metachelifer cheni sp. nov., holotype male (A-J) and paratype female (K) A carapace B left chelicera C right leg I, lateral view D right leg IV, lateral view E coxa IV, ventral view F palp (minus chela) G chela, retrolateral view H chela, dorsal view I male genital area J male genitalia, dorsal view K female genital area. Scale bars: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.78808.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691634" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">1B</figureCitation>
). Galea with a short, broad stump on left chelicera (clearly broken). Serrula exterior with about 21-22 blades. Rallum with 3 blades, anterior 1 weakly denticulate distally. 
<emphasis id="19F402A62F4F96E0D00B8EDE5FCF3B1F" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Pedipalp</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="64F659A0A2A5E3C1AEC8B8DCB56AAAE8" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Metachelifer cheni sp. nov., holotype male (A-J) and paratype female (K) A carapace B left chelicera C right leg I, lateral view D right leg IV, lateral view E coxa IV, ventral view F palp (minus chela) G chela, retrolateral view H chela, dorsal view I male genital area J male genitalia, dorsal view K female genital area. Scale bars: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.78808.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691634" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">1F-H</figureCitation>
): all segments with well-developed granulations, except for chelal fingers, which are smooth; dorsal setae short and prominently denticuloclavate. Trochanter 1.92-1.95 
<normalizedToken id="5BBD66828412B4FA37976E87C66EFD9A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
, femur 6.55-6.57 
<normalizedToken id="4EE09707946DDE31AAFC0AD446BF2F9D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
, patella 5.29-5.33 
<normalizedToken id="3E88C5CA099A174440DE8CFEF7B978D2" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than broad. Femur 1.13-1.14 
<normalizedToken id="7CE8AE2328B7F9044CDAAA8D0999C75B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than patella. Chela with pedicel 6.10-6.12 
<normalizedToken id="6A76E8BB51B5FEC9EDA9F2681572F96A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
, hand with pedicel 3.06-3.08 
<normalizedToken id="76DFE8F06B52F000D853FEBA113ECD14" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than broad; movable chelal finger 1.03-1.04 
<normalizedToken id="AFBB7667B79843B9707BF83378512527" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than hand with pedicel length. Fixed finger with 64-66 small cusped teeth, movable finger with 63-65 teeth; venom apparatus present in both chelal fingers very short (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F6F52634343F14BD8AFD0E35F3C820F8" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Metachelifer cheni sp. nov., holotype male (A-J) and paratype female (K) A carapace B left chelicera C right leg I, lateral view D right leg IV, lateral view E coxa IV, ventral view F palp (minus chela) G chela, retrolateral view H chela, dorsal view I male genital area J male genitalia, dorsal view K female genital area. Scale bars: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.78808.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691634" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">1G</figureCitation>
). Fixed chelal finger with 8 trichobothria and movable finger with 4, 
<emphasis id="A4BCE9EC955B47A989C92FDFDA4D491E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">eb</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="2CAD065D67C16A293383642AE46D8CB4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">esb</emphasis>
(retrolateral view) and 
<emphasis id="7DBE9E7AB034BC4BB581781D6CA51296" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">ib-isb</emphasis>
(dorsal view) at the base of the fixed finger; 
<emphasis id="DD764A1BFC9E6EE9EBA6018E93B1A868" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">est</emphasis>
in finger middle, 
<emphasis id="79D2663562AD521C153D60BE99312D88" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">et</emphasis>
distinctly closer to fingertip than to 
<emphasis id="4836036CFBBD39B0B00CAC4A8D3443F5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">it</emphasis>
; on movable finger, 
<emphasis id="3FF638FC9214BBDDB5997A750552AD65" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">st</emphasis>
nearer to 
<emphasis id="9425AE26EAB174CF20230B2E6B416549" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">sb</emphasis>
than to 
<emphasis id="8DAA8092764E07BE2DC5AE5F8E043A95" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">t.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="0BD44A563B3EAC8B51B5624D5A2D6669" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Opisthosoma</emphasis>
: tergal chaetotaxy (I-XI): 10: 12: 13: 14: 16: 16: 14: 19: 19: 15: 12; sternal chaetotaxy (IV-XI): 2 
<normalizedToken id="DBEFCF4A69702CF2E248AC4ABF5D3C07" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2 + 9: 11: 12: 12: 10: 14: 10: 9; anal cone with 2 dorsal and 2 ventral setae. Tergite XI with 2 tactile setae. Anterior genital operculum with 73-74 setae and 2 lyrifissures; posterior operculum with 16-17 setae, 7-8 lyrifissures (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="65480019E00C2C9CEECE6D28601CF0E2" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Metachelifer cheni sp. nov., holotype male (A-J) and paratype female (K) A carapace B left chelicera C right leg I, lateral view D right leg IV, lateral view E coxa IV, ventral view F palp (minus chela) G chela, retrolateral view H chela, dorsal view I male genital area J male genitalia, dorsal view K female genital area. Scale bars: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.78808.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691634" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">1I</figureCitation>
). Structure of male genitalia as illustrated (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F18C08AA2E6BA66396D1368433B478EE" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Metachelifer cheni sp. nov., holotype male (A-J) and paratype female (K) A carapace B left chelicera C right leg I, lateral view D right leg IV, lateral view E coxa IV, ventral view F palp (minus chela) G chela, retrolateral view H chela, dorsal view I male genital area J male genitalia, dorsal view K female genital area. Scale bars: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.78808.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691634" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">1J</figureCitation>
); eversible sacs large; apodeme of eversible sac and lateral apodeme well developed. 
