</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AAF075C002AAD5EC2196543D51251E7D" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis id="44B358FE5707F40EA58DC3DE1BD5FAF4" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Carapace</emphasis>
: slightly longer than broad (1.12-1.13 
<normalizedToken id="391A1FB346921D653E171D40B34BCC9E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
), anterior margin with 6 setae, posterior margin with 12-13 setae. Well-developed paramedian impressions behind eyes as in male. 
<emphasis id="78403A7766A65D7924468E0C2A6CEF78" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Coxae</emphasis>
: pedipalpal coxa with 14 setae, coxa I 12-15, II 19-21, III 22-25, IV 33-38. 
<emphasis id="CD33E19D5A2C98CD24C07A9E4F8825AD" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Chelicera</emphasis>
: 1.98-2.01 
<normalizedToken id="8BC2F8FC85D43010A8DD8CB13A21E78F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than broad, movable finger with 3 teeth. 
<emphasis id="39EDF071CB84F34A0E08B76B8AF87F24" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Pedipalp</emphasis>
: trochanter 2.07-2.09 
<normalizedToken id="C28D1F68504BE11DDCA7290BA4BDEDFB" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than broad, femur 6.46-6.48 
<normalizedToken id="9F4E13CE25A85290009E756BF169498E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than broad, patella 5.11-5.15 
<normalizedToken id="759958A953851B581AF333EAD1225E63" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than broad, femur 1.12-1.13 
<normalizedToken id="623C674AE1974271D331ECD61F09213E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than patella. Chela with pedicel 5.53-5.56 
<normalizedToken id="C146E375B56089E3EBB8E9E0D6795300" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than broad, hand with pedicel 2.82-2.84 
<normalizedToken id="A817BE78B06610E4D570333931565ABB" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than broad; movable finger 1.02-1.03 
<normalizedToken id="9E3266CE23423A9D4A1A0D026396C1F7" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than hand with pedicel length. 
<emphasis id="1B6259C4480DB01155057B7B9E1DC278" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">Opisthosoma</emphasis>
: tergal chaetotaxy (I-XI): 11: 14: 13: 14: 16: 18: 18: 18: 18: 16: 9; sternal chaetotaxy (IV-XI): 2 
<normalizedToken id="ACCCD5DB2F0735534ACB2B9E5C21691A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1 + 9: 15: 12: 13: 11: 14: 14: 7; anal cone with 2 dorsal and 2 ventral setae. Anterior genital operculum with 31 setae (24 of them tubular) and 2 lyrifissures; posterior operculum with 12 setae, without lyrifissures (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EA3507885BD95A6A9CFD58C668DC55A1" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Metachelifer cheni sp. nov., holotype male (A-J) and paratype female (K) A carapace B left chelicera C right leg I, lateral view D right leg IV, lateral view E coxa IV, ventral view F palp (minus chela) G chela, retrolateral view H chela, dorsal view I male genital area J male genitalia, dorsal view K female genital area. Scale bars: 0.50 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.78808.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691634" pageId="0" pageNumber="171">1K</figureCitation>
). Sternites with 2 lateral cribriform plates.
</paragraph>
